*****
[5] Switzerland
Date: Wed 1 Jun 2011
Source: World Radio [edited]
http://worldradio.ch/wrs/news/wrsnews/another-swiss-e-coli-case-reported.shtml?24902


A 2nd person in Switzerland is ill from _E. coli_ after a trip to
Germany, following a deadly outbreak [caused by] bacteria-infected
produce across Europe.

The Swiss Federal Office of Public Health says the most recent case
comes after another person was infected after a trip to northern
Germany. Both individuals are in stable condition and the illness is
running its course in each case. So far, no contaminated produce has
been identified in Switzerland.

Swiss health officials say Switzerland sees about 60 cases of illness
annually from [EHEC] _E. coli_. So far this year far there have been
23 cases, a normal amount.

